<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="782" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d782">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/12–1049</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State for Far
                            Eastern Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Butterworth</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-12-10">December 10, 1949</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Symptomatic of the difficulties inherent in China which operate against any
                        Chinese Government under present circumstances is the fact that the official
                        rate of exchange between the U.S. dollar and the Communist currency has
                        moved since April of this year from 1 to 600 to the present 1 to 18,000.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>W. W[<hi rend="smallcaps">alton</hi>] B[<hi rend="smallcaps">utterworth</hi>]</signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>